<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF9C6A23FF8A9B191DD7B6BA" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF9C6A23FF8A9B191DD7B6BA" blockId="103.[116,1323,3352,3472]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">
Previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF9C6A23FE469B191C65B653" baseAuthorityName="Cretzschmar" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[442,613,3392,3425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Barbastella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucomelas">B. leucomelas</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF9C6A23FD6B9B191D6AB653" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[663,874,3392,3425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Barbastella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="darjelingensis">B. darjelingensis</taxonomicName>
; recently separated as a distinct species based on morphometric and genetic data. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF9C6A23F827974C166EBAE6" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FF9C6A23F827974C166EBAE6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398275" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398275/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" targetBox="[1395,1987,286,700]" targetPageId="103">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF9C6A23F827974C166EBAE6" blockId="103.[2010,2603,277,705]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF9C6A23F827974C1693BA04" bold="true" box="[2011,2195,277,310]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">Distribution.</emphasis>
E Caucasus and N 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF9C6A23F637974C1406BA04" box="[2507,2566,277,310]" name="Iran" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">Iran</collectingCountry>
E to W 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFF9C6A23F7D2971B16CBBA6D" box="[2094,2251,322,351]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
. Due to recent reclassification of the species and lack of samples, current distribution is very poorly delimited.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF9C6A23F8279783165DBF79" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF9C6A23F8279783165DBF79" blockId="103.[2010,2603,277,705]" lastBlockId="103.[1395,2606,711,1454]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFF9C6A23F827978316D5BAC9" bold="true" box="[2011,2261,474,507]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F67297831423BAC9" box="[2446,2595,474,507]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="54.0" valueMax="63.0" valueMin="45.0">45-63 mm</quantity>
, tail 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F7E7945E16BCB916" box="[2075,2236,519,548]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="45.0" valueMax="50.0" valueMin="40.0">40-50 mm</quantity>
, ear c.15&gt; mm, forearm 40-6-44- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F7AF947016B5B978" box="[2131,2229,553,586]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
; weight 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F6BB947017B1B978" box="[2375,2481,553,586]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="0.6" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="g" value="12.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="6.0">6-18 g</quantity>
. Fur is soft and long (
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F73E940C175CB940" box="[2242,2396,597,626]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10-13 mm</quantity>
on back and 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F8279421165FB9AB" box="[2011,2143,632,665]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="9.0">9-10 mm</quantity>
on belly); very distinctive, hairs with dark brown or blackish bases (onehalf of their length) and whitish or pale brown distal parts; almost white on belly. Ears lack typical rounded or circular lobe on outer margin of other barbastelles; when flattened, ears pass tip of muzzle by 2- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F868954F1606B805" box="[1940,2054,790,823]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2-5 mm</quantity>
. Muzzle, ears, and limbs are brownish, but paler than body skin. Wings long and narrow. Distal vertebra oftail is free. Skull shape and size are very similar to those of European morphotypes; frontal part of skull has deeper slope with anterior part less bulbous than in closest relatives; basial pits and zygomatic arches weakly developed; greatest skull length c.15- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F6B395EA17A4B8E6" box="[2383,2468,947,980]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
; condylobasal length 13- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F9A6958218DDB8CE" box="[1626,1757,987,1020]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="11.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="7.0">7-15 mm</quantity>
; and upper tooth row length 4-8- 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFF9C6A23F73E95821719B8CE" box="[2242,2329,987,1020]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
. P? tiny and almost entirely hidden behind cingulum of C'; I? is bicuspid; upper molars poorly developed. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 32 and FN = 50.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF9C6A23FA89920818D3BF40" box="[1397,1747,1105,1138]" pageId="103" pageNumber="861" type="biology_ecology">
